article.headline: Niagara 77, Rider 52
article.story: BRIDGEPORT, Conn. (AP) -- Charron Fisher's 16 points and 11 rebounds led Niagara to a 77-52 victory over Rider in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference quarterfinals Saturday. The No. 2-seeded Purple Eagles (20-11), who advanced to Sunday's semifinals, also received 15 points and 12 rebounds from Clif Brown. Lorenzo Miles and Tyrone Lewis added 12 points each. Rider (16-15) received 22 points and nine rebounds from Jason Thompson and 11 points from Lamar Johnson. The seventh-seeded Broncs committed 17 turnovers and were outrebounded 47-29. Niagara shot only 39.1 percent from the floor, but made all 12 of its foul shots. The Purple Eagles were 11 of 33 from 3-point range on a night when Rider went 6 of 20 from that distance. The Purple Eagles surged to a 36-18 halftime lead, but Rider responded in the second half and pulled within eight points on Thompson's layup with 7:55 remaining. Niagara then iced the game with a 19-4 run over the ensuing three minutes.
